  keywords = {ME/CFS, prognosis, diagnostic delay, recovery, early intervention},
  note = {Retrospective longitudinal study (n=168, median 55-month follow-up) identifying diagnostic delay as critical prognostic factor. Recovered/improved patients had median 23-month diagnostic delay vs 55 months for non-recovered (p=0.0004). Multivariate analysis: diagnostic delay inversely associated with recovery/improvement (OR 0.98, p=0.036). Older age at onset paradoxically associated with better outcomes (OR 1.06, p=0.028). Recovery rate 8.3\%, improvement 4.8\%. Demonstrates critical window for intervention and importance of early diagnosis}
